    housing  a  basic  need  for  humans  could play  an  important  role  in  accommodating  high  urban  growth  in  india    with  more than  one  crore  population  getting  added  to  urban  areas  indias  urban  population  is expected to reach about 81 crore by 2050  as per studies conducted by the ministry of rural development and the ministry of housing and urban poverty alleviation it  is  estimated  that  almost  a  quarter  of  indian  households  lack  adequate  housing facility    the  revised  estimate  for  the  year  201516  was  reported  as  2364  crore rupees  which  is  significantly  lesser  than  the  budgeted  estimate  for  housing  for  the same  year  ie  56343  crore  rupees    i  would  urge  the  government  to  look  into  the reasons  for  the  significantly  lower  revised  budget  estimates  for  the  year  201516  the need of the hour is to strengthen the ulbs as of now most of the solid waste are  going  into  land  fill  sites  without  any  treatment    therefore  special  interest  in case of solid waste management is the need of the hour   